resources.string:
Since a device administrator must be activated in order to start the main service, uninstalling LockscreenEar could be complicated; therefore the procedure can be carried out below in two steps:

1) Deactivation, if active, of the device administrator;

2) Actual uninstallation

The following accessibility service undertakes only to LOCK THE SCREEN when:
1) any action is taken to bypass the lock screen, if active, offered by LockscreenEar;
2) the main service gets started via quick setting;
3) this service gets started (a situation that also occurs when the screen is booted), if explicitly requested via settings.

In no case your personal data will be collected
